Across 25 iterations, I first screened single-feature associations with objective_response using two-proportion z-tests. Binary features were compared as 1 vs 0; multi-valued numeric features were compared as upper quartile vs lower quartile so every effect estimate is an absolute response-probability difference. 13 of 75 features had nominal p<0.05, and 11 remained significant after Benjamini-Hochberg correction. The strongest single-feature signals were:
